urnal", "Kennebec journal"], "partof": ["serial and government publications division", "chronicling america", "catalog", "daily kennebec journal (augusta, me.) 1870-1975", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "daily kennebec journal (augusta, me.) 1870-1975 [microfilm reel]"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 67.98902, "shelf_id": "Newspaper", "site": ["chroniclingamerica", "usnd", "catalog"], "subject": ["augusta (me.)", "newspapers", "maine", "https://id.oclc.org/worldcat/entity/e39qbtfrbtwdtqxpcmbqmjkqxm", "kennebec county", "united states", "https://id.oclc.org/worldcat/entity/e39qbtfrqfrccwcp3kwyyxx9km", "kennebec county (me.)", "kennebec", "augusta"], "timestamp": "2026-07-18T09:02:06.495Z", "title": "Daily Kennebec journal", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn82014248/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sn93066937/"], "batch": ["me_journaux_ver04"], "campaigns": [], "date": "191?", "description": ["Weekly Place of publication also given as: Waterville. In French. Description based on: Vol. 1, no 39 (29 oct. 1911)."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-06-05T18:25:13.325Z", "group": ["newspaper-titles", "ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn93066937/", "image_url": [], "index": 7, "language": ["french"], "latlong": [44.5528386, -69.6313087], "location": ["waterville", "maine", "united states", "kennebec", "augusta"], "location_str": "", "lonlat": [-69.6313087, 44.5528386], "number": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sn93066937/1911-10-29/ed-1/", "2025-04-13t02:10:16.180985", "maine state libr", "assumption university", "27801260", "microform", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "sn93066937", "online resource", "1", "microfilm service copy"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["serial and government publications division", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "chronicling america", "la revue (augusta, me.) 191?-191?"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 34.15179, "shelf_id": "http://lccn.loc.gov/sn93066937", "site": ["chroniclingamerica", "usnd"], "subject": ["waterville", "waterville (me.)", "newspapers", "maine", "augusta (me.)", "united states", "french-canadians", "kennebec", "french", "augusta"], "timestamp": "2026-07-18T09:34:54.096Z", "title": "La revue", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn93066937/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2024271101/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["methodist episcopal church, south"], "date": "1837", "dates": ["[1837 TO 1948]"], "description": ["Weekly Print began with vol. I, number 1 (June 24, 1837); ceased with volume 112, number 46 (November 18, 1948). \"Began as a newspaper but gradually developed a periodical format\"--Moore, South Carolina newspapers, page 210. Published: Charleston, South Carolina, 1837-1862 and 1878-1886; Augusta, Georgia, 1862-1865; Macon, Georgia, 1866-1878; Columbia, South Carolina, 1887-1894, 1899-1900 and 1919-1948; Greenville, South Carolina, 1895-1898 and 1912-1914; Orangeburg, South Carolina, 1901-1902; Spartanburg, South Carolina, 1903-1912; and Anderson, South Carolina, 1915-1918. Volumes for 1866- numbered continuously as whole no. 1465- . Issue of <Dec. 18, 1862> called also: <New ser., v. 1, no. 30> Issues for <Mar. 23, 1865> lack volume numbering. Publication suspended Apr. 20-June 22, 1865 and July 6-Aug. 24, 1865. Published for: Methodist Episcopal Church, 1837-<June 6, 1845>; for the Methodist Episcopal Church, South, <June 12, 1846>-1899; for the South Carolina Conference of the Methodist Episcopal Church, South, 1900. Mirror of the times (Macon, Ga.) may have been intended to appear also as a separately titled section of this publication. Vol. VII, No. 1, Whole Number 313 (June 16, 1843); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed April 24, 2024). Vol. 67, No. 28 (December 31, 1903) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed April 24, 2024). South Carolina Methodist advocate"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:38:15Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2024271101/", "image_url": [], "index": 8, "language": ["english"], "location": ["anderson", "richmond", "spartanburg", "georgia", "bibb", "greenville", "columbia", "united states", "orangeburg", "southern states", "richland", "macon", "south carolina", "charleston", "augusta"], "number": ["online resource", "2024271101", "1431124435", "2997-5689", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["May sometimes be called: Southern advocate"], "partof": ["serial and government publications division", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "southern christian advocate (charleston, s.c.) 1837-1948 [online resource]"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 16.928211, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD BX8201 .S6", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["anderson", "richmond", "columbia", "united states", "southern states", "orangeburg", "spartanburg", "georgia", "newspapers", "macon", "methodist episcopal church, south", "charleston", "bibb", "methodists", "augusta", "periodicals", "richland", "south carolina", "greenville"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T21:13:38.179Z", "title": "Southern Christian advocate", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2024271101/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2011254047/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1889", "dates": ["[1889 TO 1904]"], "description": ["Weekly Print began in 1889; ceased in 1904. Description based on: Vol. 11, no. 26 (Jan. 27, 1900); title from PDF masthead (Readex America's Historical Newspapers Web site, viewed Apr. 27, 2011). Latest issue consulted: Vol. 11, no. 26 (Jan. 27, 1900) (viewed Apr. 27, 2011)."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:14.323Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspape